---
import Band from "../components/Band.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHero from "../components/PageHero.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="VaporHuman"
  canonicalPath="/"
  currentPath="/"
>
  <PageHero
    home
    kicker="Private AI continuity systems"
    title="VaporHuman"
    lede="Turn scattered AI work into a private, usable system with trust boundaries, memory, handoffs, and human approval built in."
    body="VaporHuman helps owner-operated teams and serious builders make AI assistance practical without losing control of context, decisions, or public claims."
  >
    <div class="button-row" aria-label="Featured pages">
      <a class="button" href="/work.html">Work with VaporHuman</a>
      <a class="button button--ghost" href="/trust.html">Review the trust boundary</a>
    </div>
  </PageHero>

  <Band
    variant="intro"
    kicker="What it does"
    title="A private operating layer for AI work."
    id="questions-title"
  >
    <ol class="question-list">
      <li>Keep important context reusable across tools, sessions, and assistants.</li>
      <li>Make decisions, approvals, and stop lines visible before work goes public.</li>
      <li>Turn messy assistant output into repeatable workflows people can use.</li>
    </ol>
  </Band>

  <Band kicker="Offer" title="Built for people already using AI seriously." id="what-title" columns>
    <ul class="principles">
      <li>assistant workflow audits</li>
      <li>private continuity maps</li>
      <li>repo and product handoff systems</li>
      <li>support knowledge architecture</li>
      <li>approval gates for public work</li>
      <li>operator dashboards after provider review</li>
    </ul>
  </Band>

  <Band
    variant="boundary"
    kicker="What this is not"
    title="Not A Substitute For Human Judgment"
    id="not-title"
  >
    <p>
      VaporHuman is not a person, therapist, doctor, lawyer, accountant,
      employer, identity service, emergency service, or authority over human
      decisions.
    </p>
    <p>
      It does not promise that AI is always right, always safe, private by
      default, always available, or a substitute for human judgment.
    </p>
  </Band>

  <Band kicker="Why it exists" title="Keep The Human Visible" id="why-title" columns>
    <div>
      <p>AI work gets expensive when every session restarts from zero. VaporHuman goes the other way.</p>
      <p>
        The goal is to make assistant systems more useful in practice: what
        they know, what they do not know, what they are allowed to do, what
        should stay private, and when a human needs to approve the next move.
      </p>
      <p>
        Start with <a href="/work.html">Work with VaporHuman</a>, then read the
        <a href="/trust.html">Trust boundary</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Band>

  <Band variant="status" kicker="Private beta" title="Useful before it is loud." id="status-title" columns>
    <div>
      <p>
        VaporHuman should become useful first in private, controlled workflows,
        then graduate public lead capture, payments, and analytics only after
        the provider gates are selected and verified.
      </p>
      <p class="principle">Useful first. Honest always. Human in charge.</p>
    </div>
  </Band>
</BaseLayout>
